EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 132300 UTC
FRIDAY EVENING A WEAK RIDGE WILL EXTEND ACROSS THE UK WITH AN ANTICYCLONIC
CENTRE 1033 CENTRED OVER SCANDINAVIA AND A FURTHER ANTICYCLONIC CENTRE
1025 NEAR THE AZORES. AN ATLANTIC LOW 982 LIES SLOW MOV SW OF ICELAND.
DURING SATURDAY NIGHT AND SUNDAY A SECOND LOW IS FCST TO DEVELOP TO THE W
OF NITON AND MOV N W OF PORTPATRICK TO LIE S OF ICELAND BY MIDDAY MONDAY.
THE AZORES HIGH IS THEN EXP TO EXTEND NWARDS IN ITS WAKE. GALES ARE NOT EXP
ACROSS NITON HOWEVER WINDS COULD BECOME STRG ACROSS SHANNON FRIDAY NIGHT
INTO SATURDAY AND PERHAPS APPROACHING STRG WINDS OR NEAR GALE ONCE AGAIN
IN SHANNON SATURDAY NIGHT INTO SUNDAY MORNING AS WELL AS ACROSS SW FITZROY
LATER ON MONDAY. AREAS OF FOG POSS PORTLAND PLYMOUTH LUNDY FASTNET AND
